olves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Weaknesses: regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills. Also later we have moody, loner.\n\nWe have all strengths listed. However, we might be missing some strengths for some candidates that other agents might have. For example, we haven't seen any strengths for D beyond those four. We asked earlier and got none. For A, we have strengths listed. For B, we have strengths listed. For C, we have strengths listed. So we have full strengths.\n\nBut we might be missing weaknesses for some candidates that could affect decision. We have many weaknesses listed. For A: not good at criticism, unorganized. For B: grumpy, uncooperative, pretentious, wrong tone. For C: difficulty communicating, egocentric, not willing to further education. For D: arrogant, weak leadership, moody, loner.\n\nWe have all.\n\nNow we need to produce public message: share reasoning, maybe ask if any other strengths for D? Already asked earlier, none. Could ask about any additional weaknesses for D? Not required but could be helpful. But we have weaknesses for D.\n\nWe need to decide vote. In previous rounds, Agent 3 voted B, Agent 1 earlier also voted B. So consensus leaning B. But we must still consider if any missing info could change view. Perhaps we lack any strengths for D beyond problem solving, responsibility. Could D have other strengths like \"excellent navigation skills\"? Not known. So we cannot assume.\n\nThus we likely also vote B.\n\nWe should also ask other agents if they have any additional strengths for D or any other candidate we might be missing. But we already asked earlier and got none. Could ask about any additional strengths for D? Already asked. Could ask about any additional strengths for A? Already asked. For C? Already asked. For B? Already asked. So we have all.\n\nThus we can present reasoning and vote.\n\nPublic message: Summarize each candidate's strengths/weaknesses, weigh against criteria, note that B's reliability and calmness are top, while other candidates have more critical weaknesses (communication, teamwork, health). Conclude vote for B.\n\nWe must output only two sections.\n\nProceed."}
